CNCP v1 23990
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5900: Support default export in namespaced components syntax",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:21.351626+00:00",
  "text": "Support default export in namespaced components syntax\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\r\nSince version 3.2.0 Vue supports [Namespaced Components](https://vuejs.org/api/sfc-script-setup.html#namespaced-components) syntax. However, it expects all components to be exported as named exports, therefore [this example](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#) does not work.\r\n\r\n### What does the proposed API look like?\r\nI would simply like to use the following syntax:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// components/Dropdown.js\r\nexport default function Dropdown() {}\r\nexport function Toggle() {}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<script setup>\r\n  import * as Dropdown from 'components/Dropdown'\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<template>\r\n  <Dropdown>\r\n    <Dropdown.Toggle>click me</Dropdown.Toggle>\r\n  </Dropdown>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\ninstead of\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<template>\r\n  <Dropdown.default>...</Dropdown.default>\r\n  <Dropdown.Dropdown>...</Dropdown.Dropdown>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlso, while we're on the subject. Why doesn't this syntax work when components are imported outside of script-setup (in a regular script block). is there any reason for this limitation? Thank you for your consideration.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
